{{Same-sex unions}}
<!--- *** Please do not edit the introduction without achieving consensus on the talk (discussion) page first. *** --->
'''Same-sex marriage''', also known as '''gay marriage''', is [[marriage]] between [[same-sex relationship|people of the same sex]], either as a secular [[Civil marriage|civil ceremony]] or in a religious setting.

In the late 20th century, religious rites of marriage without legal recognition became increasingly common. The first law providing for marriage of people of the same sex in modern times was enacted in 2001 in the [[Netherlands]]. {{As of|2015|11|16|df=y}}, fourteen countries ([[Same-sex marriage in Argentina|Argentina]], [[Same-sex marriage in Belgium|Belgium]], [[Same-sex marriage in Brazil|Brazil]], [[Same-sex marriage in Canada|Canada]], [[Same-sex marriage in France|France]], [[Same-sex marriage in Iceland|Iceland]], [[Same-sex marriage in Ireland|Ireland]], [[Same-sex marriage in Luxembourg|Luxembourg]], [[Same-sex marriage in Norway|Norway]], [[Same-sex marriage in Portugal|Portugal]], [[Same-sex marriage in South Africa|South Africa]], [[Same-sex marriage in Spain|Spain]], [[Same-sex marriage in Sweden|Sweden]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Uruguay|Uruguay]]) and certain sub-jurisdictions (parts of [[Kingdom of Denmark|Denmark]],<ref group="nb" name="Denmark">[[Same-sex marriage in Denmark|Denmark proper]]. In Greenland, a law providing for same-sex marriage is not yet in force.</ref> [[Same-sex marriage in Mexico|Mexico]],<ref group="nb" name="Mexico">[[Same-sex marriage in Chihuahua|Chihuahua]], [[Same-sex marriage in Coahuila|Coahuila]], [[Same-sex marriage in Guerrero|Guerrero]], [[Same-sex marriage in Quintana Roo|Quintana Roo]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Mexico City|Federal District]].</ref> the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands|Netherlands]],<ref group="nb" name="Netherlands">[[Same-sex marriage in the Netherlands|The Netherlands proper]].</ref> [[Realm of New Zealand|New Zealand]],<ref group="nb" name="New Zealand">[[Same-sex marriage in New Zealand|New Zealand proper]].</ref> the [[Same-sex marriage in the United Kingdom|United Kingdom]]<ref group="nb" name="United Kingdom">[[England and Wales]], [[Scotland]] and [[Same-sex marriage in the Pitcairn Islands|the Pitcairn Islands]], notably excluding [[Northern Ireland]]</ref> and the [[Same-sex marriage in the United States|United States]]<ref group="nb" name="United States">United States proper, [[Same-sex marriage in Guam|Guam]], [[Same-sex marriage in the Northern Mariana Islands|the Northern Mariana Islands]], [[Same-sex marriage in Puerto Rico|Puerto Rico]], [[Same-sex marriage in the United States Virgin Islands|the United States Virgin Islands]] and [[Same-sex marriage under United States tribal jurisdictions|some tribal jurisdictions]].</ref>) allow same-sex couples to marry. Similar law in [[Same-sex marriage in Finland|Finland]] is not yet in force. Polls show rising support for legally recognizing same-sex marriage in [[LGBT rights in the Americas|the Americas]], [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Australia|Australia]] and most of [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Europe|Europe]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Poll shows growing support for same-sex marriage|url=http://www.smh.com.au/federal-politics/political-news/poll-shows-growing-support-for-samesex-marriage-20140714-3bxaj.html|publisher=Sydney Morning Herald|accessdate=22 May 2015|date=15 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=For several years a majority of Australians have supported marriage equality|url=http://www.australianmarriageequality.org/who-supports-equality/a-majority-of-australians-support-marriage-equality/|publisher=Australian Marriage Equality Incorporated|accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>See
* {{cite web|last=Newport|first=Frank|title=For First Time, Majority of Americans Favor Legal Gay Marriage|url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/147662/First-Time-Majority-Americans-Favor-Legal-Gay-Marriage.aspx|publisher=[[The Gallup Organization|Gallup]]|accessdate=25 September 2012}}
* {{cite web|title=Support for Same‐Sex Marriage in Latin America|url=http://www.vanderbilt.edu/lapop/insights/I0844.enrevised.pdf|publisher=[[Vanderbilt University]]|accessdate=25 September 2012}}</ref>
However, as of 2015 South Africa is the only African country where same-sex marriage is recognized, and none of the Asian countries have recognized same-sex marriage.

